**The Delta Method.** Let $X_{1},…,X_{n}$ be i.i.d.\ with mean $\mu>0$ and variance $\sigma^{2}$. \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item State the Delta Method for smooth $g$.

\item Apply to find the asymptotic distribution of $\sqrt{n}(1/\bar{X}_{n} - 1/\mu)$.

\item Apply to find the asymptotic distribution of $\sqrt{n}(\log\bar{X}_{n} - \log\mu)$.\end{enumerate}

**CLT for Sample Variance.** Let $X_{1},…,X_{n}\stackrel{\text{iid}}{\sim}N(\mu,\sigma^{2})$. Let $S^{2} = \frac{1}{n-1}\sum_{i=1}^{n}(X_{i}-\bar{X})^{2}$. \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item Show $(n-1)S^{2}/\sigma^{2}\sim\chi^{2}(n-1)$.

\item Is $S^{2}$ an unbiased estimator of $\sigma^{2}$?

\item What is the asymptotic distribution of $\sqrt{n}(S^{2}-\sigma^{2})$?\end{enumerate}

**Slutsky's Theorem Application.** Suppose $X_{n}\xrightarrow{d}N(0,1)$ and $Y_{n}\xrightarrow{p}2$. \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item State Slutsky's Theorem.

\item Limiting distribution of $X_{n}/Y_{n}$.

\item Limiting distribution of $X_{n} + Y_{n}$.\end{enumerate}
